    "GraphAide's query phase begins with a natural language user query, as shown in Figure 1.",
    "User queries are often incomplete and imprecise, which can lead to reduced retrieval accuracy and relevance when using vector databases.",
    "To address query-document mismatch in sparse retrieval, LLM-based query expansion has been shown to alleviate these challenges Ayoub et al. (2024).",
    "GraphAide applies a similar approach to embedding-based dense retrieval, using a template-based method to generate additional versions of the input query while preserving the key entities and relationships mentioned in the original query.",
    "Subsequently, GraphAide leverages LLMs to convert the expanded set of queries into attributed subgraph matching templates, as illustrated in Figure 1."
